| Tailwind Version | Dark Mode Config |
|---|---|
| v3 | `darkMode: "class"` in `tailwind.config.js` |
| v4 | `@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));` in your global CSS |

One of the features of this new version of Tailwind is that configurations can be made in a single `global.css` file. The key is ensuring `next-themes` adds the `.dark` class to `<html>`, and Tailwind v4's `@custom-variant` is set up to respond to that class.


